1
00:00:05,298 --> 00:00:09,437
We know, the same time,
some of the superior devotee

2
00:00:09,437 --> 00:00:11,817
like Kṛṣṇadās Bābājī Mahārāj—

3
00:00:11,817 --> 00:00:13,537
I’ve been a witness,

4
00:00:13,537 --> 00:00:16,152
and Guru Mahārāj mentioned it 
on his disappearance day,

5
00:00:16,152 --> 00:00:17,748
once, in praise of him—

6
00:00:17,766 --> 00:00:26,024
the whole night chanting 
Kṛṣṇa-nām and kīrtan songs.

7
00:00:26,024 --> 00:00:29,154
[Ekadashi | From Dusk Till Dawn]

8
00:00:29,704 --> 00:00:35,079
And once in Māyāpur that night 
we were in this room with him,

9
00:00:35,079 --> 00:00:37,890
and devotees were asking him
different questions,

10
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:41,761
and he was giving that answer,
“Hare Kṛṣṇa!”

11
00:00:42,439 --> 00:00:46,804
So, someone said, “Bābājī Mahārāj, 
how to overcome sex desire?”

12
00:00:46,912 --> 00:00:51,435
He said, “You are trying! 
I am trying! Hare Kṛṣṇa!”

13
00:00:51,587 --> 00:00:53,950
[Laughing]

14
00:00:53,950 --> 00:00:56,644
We got some encouragement.

15
00:00:57,465 --> 00:01:02,822
But, anyway, that night as we all ...
It was like eleven, twelve …

16
00:01:02,822 --> 00:01:06,818
I remember, I got to play the drum
at one point,

17
00:01:06,818 --> 00:01:09,275
and he went like, 
“Give me the drum!”

18
00:01:09,275 --> 00:01:13,462
[Laughing]

19
00:01:13,462 --> 00:01:16,955
First I was like, “Wow! …” 
and he’s saying …

20
00:01:19,408 --> 00:01:21,410
[Laughing]

21
00:01:21,410 --> 00:01:25,426
But, anyway, kept singing and we also …
Then now it’s midnight …

22
00:01:25,426 --> 00:01:31,656
He doesn’t show any signs 
of, like, fatigue.

23
00:01:31,748 --> 00:01:35,802
And then finally, we are all like falling;
then now we’re all asleep.

24
00:01:35,802 --> 00:01:41,672
And we went to sleep 
to the sound of him taking Kṛṣṇa-nām.

25
00:01:41,672 --> 00:01:46,210
And when we woke up at 4:15 
or whenever,

26
00:01:46,210 --> 00:01:49,426
there was just, 
“Hare Kṛṣṇa, Hare Kṛṣṇa”—

27
00:01:49,426 --> 00:01:51,993
he was still chanting.

28
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:56,984
So, he did that so many times.

29
00:01:57,330 --> 00:02:04,027
And I recently … 
Our godsister Deva Moyi Didi,

30
00:02:04,027 --> 00:02:07,657
she left the world,

31
00:02:07,939 --> 00:02:13,154
and she was a wonderful disciple
of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj,

32
00:02:13,154 --> 00:02:17,784
and favourite of Śrīla Gurudev,
extraordinary Vaiṣṇavī.

33
00:02:17,784 --> 00:02:21,374
When she was a little girl,

34
00:02:21,374 --> 00:02:25,524
she used to go 
to Mādhava Mahārāja’s Maṭh.

35
00:02:25,524 --> 00:02:28,116
Guru Mahārāj, whenever he mentioned 
Mādhava Mahārāja’s name,

36
00:02:28,116 --> 00:02:30,691
he’d have to go,
“Hayagrīva Brahmachārī.”

37
00:02:30,714 --> 00:02:33,314
Because he was known 
as Hayagrīva Brahmachārī

38
00:02:33,314 --> 00:02:34,469
in the Gauḍīya Maṭh.

39
00:02:34,469 --> 00:02:37,504
So even known as Mādhava Mahārāj,
this famous Mahārāj,

40
00:02:37,513 --> 00:02:40,631
established maybe twenty five Maṭhs.

41
00:02:40,973 --> 00:02:43,361
Very powerful preacher.

42
00:02:43,436 --> 00:02:45,989
Very handsome also.

43
00:02:48,110 --> 00:02:50,551
When Deva Moyi was a little girl,

44
00:02:50,551 --> 00:02:53,551
she would sometimes, like, 
sit on Mādhava—

45
00:02:53,551 --> 00:02:57,586
when she was like a toddler—
she sit on Mādhava Mahārāja’s lap,

46
00:02:57,586 --> 00:03:00,630
and he gave her some mercy,
and liked her,

47
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:05,480
she would go to his Maṭh.

48
00:03:09,149 --> 00:03:14,209
And when Śrīla Gurudev, 
when she translated things from,

49
00:03:14,209 --> 00:03:17,938
sometimes from Bengali to English
or back,

50
00:03:17,983 --> 00:03:23,106
she translated some things of Gurudev once,
some English, and he said,

51
00:03:23,106 --> 00:03:25,795
“It became better than the original.”

52
00:03:25,795 --> 00:03:27,469
[Laughing]

53
00:03:27,469 --> 00:03:31,734
He gave such praise to her.

54
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:36,900
And I had the good fortune to have 
her association at different times,

55
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:42,460
she had some affection for me,
very kind to me,

56
00:03:42,473 --> 00:03:44,445
always encouraging me.

57
00:03:44,445 --> 00:03:48,135
And once we were working 
on this publication

58
00:03:48,135 --> 00:03:51,509
called 
“Prabhupād Saraswatī Ṭhākur”,

59
00:03:51,685 --> 00:03:58,172
and I had her and her team, 
which is her daughters—

60
00:03:58,252 --> 00:04:02,755
they were always like her team,
her girls, her assistants—

61
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:06,672
doing some transliteration
and things like that.

62
00:04:06,701 --> 00:04:11,849
Anyway, I had to call her about something,
she wrote the biographical parts.

63
00:04:11,974 --> 00:04:15,692
And it was on Ekādaśī,

64
00:04:15,692 --> 00:04:20,222
and the call was there 
about 10 o’clock at night.

65
00:04:20,222 --> 00:04:24,578
And we were on the phone, and then 
we started to talk about Śrīla Guru Mahārāj

66
00:04:24,578 --> 00:04:30,059
and Mahāprabhu, Gaura-kathā,
Kṛṣṇa-kathā, Vaiṣṇava-kathā,

67
00:04:30,059 --> 00:04:36,246
and it was like midnight, 1 o’clock, then, 
I know that at a certain point,

68
00:04:36,246 --> 00:04:39,453
the sun rose.

69
00:04:40,381 --> 00:04:43,447
So we realized,

70
00:04:43,447 --> 00:04:50,267
the whole evening had been spent 
engaged in Hari-kathā.

71
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:54,354
And in a chaste way—telephone, she was
in one location, I was in another one,

72
00:04:54,354 --> 00:04:56,413
and service related ...

73
00:04:56,588 --> 00:05:05,156
But I thought, “Oh, what a personality 
that to get so absorbed

74
00:05:05,412 --> 00:05:09,206
in talking about Kṛṣṇa and Guru Mahārāj,
and all these things

75
00:05:09,206 --> 00:05:13,513
to spend the whole evening 
discussing.”

76
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:17,449
That can happen,
if it’s meant to happen.

77
00:05:17,449 --> 00:05:21,569
But, so we hear that the higher section,
they’re always,

78
00:05:21,569 --> 00:05:26,065
Bābājī Mahārāj was always doing that
every Ekādaśī.

79
00:05:26,065 --> 00:05:28,551
That was his capacity.

80
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,663
Adhikār—capacity to do that.

